uracy is very low, do not blindly union noisy lists; use a robust strategy (trusted-source selection or consensus with normalization).\n            - Always write correspondence files for every evaluated pair to `output/runs/20260322_102925_companies/correspondences/` so cluster analysis uses current run artifacts.\n            - When passing correspondences into PyDI fusion, the required schema is `id1`/`id2`. Do not invent alternate required columns such as `id_l`/`id_r`.\n            \n            11. INVESTIGATOR ACTION PLAN (RANKED):\n            [\n  {\n    "action": "Keep an attribute-specific fusion rule: strategy.add_attribute_fuser(\'city\', prefer_higher_trust, trust_map={\'fullcontact\': 3, \'dbpedia\': 2, \'forbes\': 1}) and preserve MaximumBipartiteMatching post-clustering.",\n    "target_attributes": [\n      "city"\n    ],\n    "priority_score": 0.11,\n    "confidence": 0.8,\n    "source": "investigation",\n    "attribute_class": "improvable"\n  },\n  {\n    "action": "Change founded to strategy.add_attribute_fuser(\'founded\', voting). If PyDI datetime voting is unstable in this runtime, fallback to strategy.add_attribute_fuser(\'founded\', prefer_higher_trust, trust_map={\'fullcontact\': 3, \'dbpedia\': 2, \'forbes\': 1}).",\n    "target_attributes": [\n      "founded"\n    ],\n    "priority_score": 0.09,\n    "confidence": 0.8,\n    "source": "investigation",\n    "attribute_class": "improvable"\n  },\n  {\n    "action": "If the loaded field is genuinely list-valued in PyDI, replace strategy.add_attribute_fuser(\'keypeople_name\', most_complete) with strategy.add_attribute_fuser(\'keypeople_name\', union). Otherwise preserve current rule for now.",\n    "target_attributes": [\n      "keypeople_name"\n    ],\n    "priority_score": 0.03,\n    "confidence": 0.8,\n    "source": "investigation",\n    "attribute_class": "improvable"\n  },\n  {\n    "action": "Do not change assets in pipeline_adaption; preserve current behavior and defer to normalization